<p>
In order to work with Ipfs, you need to setup an [ext[Http Api|https://docs.ipfs.io/reference/api/http/]] and an [ext[Http Gateway|https://github.com/ipfs/go-ipfs/blob/master/docs/gateway.md]] Url who will let you add, publish or unpin your ~TiddlyWiki instance and file attachments over Ipfs. 
</p>
<p>
The plugin eases the selection through drop-down lists.
</p>
<p>
<table>
<tr><th>Api Url</th><th>Tiddler</th></tr>
<tr><td>Default</td><td>[[$:/ipfs/saver/api/default]]</td></tr>
<tr><td>http://127.0.0.1:5001</td><td>[[$:/ipfs/saver/api/http/localhost/5001]]</td></tr>
<tr><td>https://ipfs.bluelightav.org</td><td>[[$:/ipfs/saver/api/https/ipfs.bluelightav.org]]</td></tr>
<tr><td>https://ipfs.infura.io:5001</td><td>[[$:/ipfs/saver/api/https/ipfs.infura.io/5001]]</td></tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
  To enhance the Api Url drop-down list, clone an existing Api Url Tiddler (see above), update the cloned Tiddler's name and update the [[Default Api Url Tiddler|$:/ipfs/saver/api/default]] if applicable.
</p>
